abstract.p:
In this paper, we study a diffusive SIRS-type epidemic model with transfer from the infectious to the susceptible class. Our model includes a general nonlinear incidence rate and spatially heterogeneous diffusion coefficients. We compute the basic reproduction number \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
